"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Wire Up Checkpoint Search via Turbopuffer\n\n## Context\n\nCheckpoints have been backfilled into Turbopuffer (namespace `checkpoints-{repo_id}`) with embeddings and attributes. The frontend currently does client-side string matching over prompts, commit messages, and authors. We need to:\n\n1. Add a search API endpoint that queries Turbopuffer\n2. Replace the frontend's client-side filtering with API-driven search\n\n## Approach\n\n- **API**: Direct `fetch()` calls to Turbopuffer REST API from the Cloudflare Worker (no new runtime dependencies)\n- **Frontend**: Replace client-side filter entirely — when search input is non-empty, call the search endpoint; when empty, show the normal checkpoint list\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts` | **Create** | Thin Turbopuffer REST client (query function) |\n| `api/src/env.ts` | **Modify** | Add optional `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` to `Env` interface |\n| `api/src/routes/cache.ts` | **Modify** | Add `GET /:org/:repo/checkpoints/search` endpoint |\n| `frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/api.ts` | **Modify** | Add `searchCheckpoints()` fetch function + response type |\n| `frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/hooks/useCommitsQuery.ts` | **Modify** | Add `useSearchCheckpointsQuery()` hook |\n| `frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/pages/CheckpointsPage.tsx` | **Modify** | Wire search input to API query, replace client-side filter |\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### 1. Turbopuffer REST Client (`api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts`)\n\nThin wrapper around Turbopuffer's REST API using `fetch()`. No SDK needed.\n\n```typescript\nexport interface TurbopufferSearchResult {\n  checkpoint_id: string;\n  // other attributes returned for convenience\n}\n\nexport async function searchCheckpoints(\n  apiKey: string,\n  repoId: string,\n  query: string,\n  filters?: { branch?: string },\n  limit?: number,\n): Promise<TurbopufferSearchResult[]>\n```\n\n**Turbopuffer REST endpoint**: `POST https://api.turbopuffer.com/v1/vectors/checkpoints-{repo_id}/query`\n\n**Request body** — use BM25 full-text search on the `text` attribute + optional attribute filters:\n```json\n{\n  \"top_k\": 50,\n  \"rank_by\": [\"text\", \"BM25\", \"search query here\"],\n  \"filters\": {\n    \"branch\": [[\"Eq\", \"main\"]]\n  },\n  \"include_attributes\": [\"checkpoint_id\"]\n}\n```\n\nReturns `checkpoint_id` values which we use to fetch full checkpoint data from PlanetScale.\n\n### 2. Env Update (`api/src/env.ts`)\n\nAdd `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY?: string` as optional to the `Env` interface. Not added to `REQUIRED_ENV_VARS` since search is an optional feature — the endpoint returns 503 if the key is missing.\n\n### 3. Search API Endpoint (`api/src/routes/cache.ts`)\n\nNew route on `repoRoutes`: `GET /:org/:repo/checkpoints/search?q=<query>&branch=<branch>`\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Validate `q` param (required, non-empty)\n2. Check repo access (reuse existing `checkRepoAccess()` helper)\n3. If `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` not set, return 503\n4. Call `searchCheckpoints()` with `repoRecord.id`, query, and optional branch filter\n5. Get the `checkpoint_id` list from results\n6. Fetch full checkpoint data from PlanetScale using existing `db.checkpoints.getByIds(repoId, checkpointIds)`\n7. Map through existing `mapCheckpointToInfo()` to build response\n8. Return in same shape as the existing checkpoints endpoint for frontend compatibility\n\n**Auth**: Same `optionalAuth + rateLimitUnauthenticated` pattern as existing checkpoint routes.\n\n**Response**: Same `CheckpointsResponse` type so the frontend can render search results identically to the normal list.\n\n### 4. Frontend API Function (`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/api.ts`)\n\nAdd:\n```typescript\nexport async function searchCheckpoints(\n  org: string, repo: string, query: string, branch?: string,\n): Promise<CheckpointsResponse> {\n  const params = new URLSearchParams({ q: query });\n  if (branch) params.set(\"branch\", branch);\n  return request<CheckpointsResponse>(\n    `/api/v1/cache/${org}/${repo}/checkpoints/search?${params.toString()}`\n  );\n}\n```\n\nReuses the existing `CheckpointsResponse` type — no new response types needed.\n\n### 5. Frontend Hook (`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/hooks/useCommitsQuery.ts`)\n\nAdd:\n```typescript\nexport function useSearchCheckpointsQuery(\n  org: string, repo: string, query: string, branch: string,\n) {\n  return useQuery<CheckpointsResponse>({\n    queryKey: [\"github\", \"checkpoints-search\", org, repo, query, branch],\n    queryFn: () => searchCheckpoints(org, repo, query, branch),\n    enabled: query.trim().length > 0,\n    staleTime: 30_000,\n    placeholderData: (prev) => prev, // keep previous results while fetching\n  });\n}\n```\n\n### 6. Frontend Page (`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/pages/CheckpointsPage.tsx`)\n\nReplace the client-side filter block (lines 82-95) with debounced API search:\n\n- Add `useEffect`-based debounce (300ms) on `searchQuery` → `debouncedQuery`\n- Call `useSearchCheckpointsQuery(org, repo, debouncedQuery, branch)`\n- When `debouncedQuery` is non-empty, use search results; otherwise use normal checkpoint list\n- Show subtle loading indicator while search is in flight\n- Update \"No matching checkpoints\" empty state to work with search results\n\nKey changes:\n- Remove: the `allCheckpoints.filter(...)` client-side logic\n- Add: `debouncedQuery` state + `useEffect` debounce\n- Add: `useSearchCheckpointsQuery` hook call\n- Modify: `checkpoints` derivation to branch on `isSearchActive`\n\n## Verification\n\n1. Set `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` via `wrangler secret put TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` for staging\n2. Start API locally with `wrangler dev` — verify search endpoint:\n   ```\n   curl \"http://localhost:8787/api/v1/cache/entireio/cli/checkpoints/search?q=authentication&branch=main\"\n   ```\n3. Start frontend locally — test search UX